<title type="html"><![CDATA[New to this, where do I begin?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6170&amp;p=58272#p58272"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">muffins wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Apparently I need something more basic.  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" /><br /></div><br />Do you also need something more visual?<br /><br />NES programs are commonly distributed in a format originally defined by a now obsolete emulator called iNES. (See <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES" class="postlink">iNES on the wiki</a>.) There are three parts to an iNES file: a 16-byte header, the PRG ROM (connected to the CPU), and the CHR ROM (connected to the PPU).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Mar 14, 2010 4:58 pm</p><hr />
